1911 Augusta Tourists/S.A.L. Orphans Roster

1911 Augusta Tourists/S.A.L. Orphans Statistics

The Augusta Tourists/S.A.L. Orphans of the South Atlantic League ended the 1911 season with a record of 52 wins and 74 lossesAugusta (42-50) forfeited franchise July 26, but the league operated the club as S.A.L. Orphans. When storms destroyed the Charleston ball park, both clubs disbanded August 30.

Jim Lafitte and Tom Stouch served as manager.
